                            <comment id="12603997" author="clint.morgan" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2008 19:34:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In hbase-669 and hbase-665 I needed to subclass these things. Here are the changes I needed. This is not a complete solution, as it only exposes what I explicitly needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604053" author="stack" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2008 21:50:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Whats this about Clint?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
@@ -220,9 +222,10 @@
     out.writeBoolean(metaregion);
     Bytes.writeByteArray(out, name);
     out.writeInt(families.size());
+    Configuration conf = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; HBaseConfiguration();
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;(Iterator&amp;lt;HColumnDescriptor&amp;gt; it = families.values().iterator();
         it.hasNext(); ) {
-      it.next().write(out);
+      ObjectWritable.writeObject(out, it.next(), HColumnDescriptor.class, conf);
     }
   }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing this an unintentional addition?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, rest of patch looks fine.  Let me know about above and I&apos;ll apply all but above changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604063" author="clint.morgan" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2008 22:16:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Above is so I can subclass HColumnDescriptor, and then put the subclass instances into the families collection and have serialization work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604069" author="stack" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2008 22:48:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, this changes the serialization format.  Means we need a migration script to bring over data that has been written with the the old Table descriptor.  See failure in the TestMigration testcase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604075" author="clint.morgan" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2008 22:58:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah.. Then lets just drop that for now. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604082" author="stack" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2008 23:53:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I applied the patch minus the HTD changes.  Thanks for the patch Clint.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
